This directory contains the JavaScript source modules for the chess UI.
These modules are merged by build-chess.py / build-chess.sh into chess.html.

License classification by file:
  - game-logic.js: GPL v3 (derived from DroidFish)
      PGN disambiguation and SAN notation logic from DroidFish.
      Copyright (C) Peter Österlund. Modifications Copyright (C) 2026 Regalia.
      v1.0.2 additions:
        - _prependBlackToMovePlaceholder(): prepends a null placeholder to
          moveRecords when a new game starts with Black to move (FEN/setup
          /PGN import paths). Syncs stateHistory[0].moveRecords so the
          placeholder survives undo back to the opening.
        - boardVersion integer on game state (incremented by makeMv /
          makeMvInPlace / _refreshStateAfterSetup, restored by unmakeMv,
          initialized to 1 by fenToState / initState) — used by the
          _updateBoardIncremental dirty check for ~100x faster render ticks.
        - moveAlg() disambiguation: replaced cloneB-per-candidate with
          makeMvInPlace/unmakeMv — eliminates up to 8 board clones per
          moveAlg call (e.g. 8 pawns that could capture on the same file).
        - pieceZobristIdx(): hoisted the {pawn:0,knight:1,...} type-index
          lookup to module scope (_PIECE_TYPE_IDX) instead of building a
          fresh object literal on every call (32+ calls per computeHash).
        - isDeadPosition(): single-pass 64-square scan with early returns
          (pawns/rooks/queens → not dead) instead of allocating a pcs[]
          array + multiple .filter()/.map() passes. Bishop square-color
          parity tracked inline. Same FIDE 5.2.2 coverage, ~3x faster.
  - ai-bridge.js: GPL v3 (derived from DroidFish)
      Engine communication patterns from DroidFish.
      Copyright (C) Peter Österlund. Modifications Copyright (C) 2026 Regalia.
      v1.0.2 additions:
        - _buildPGNString() now appends `{score eval_word}` after every
          move with a cached eval in _reviewEvalCache, and
          `{SF18 D22 +1.0 8%W/91%D/1%L}` every 5 moves (engine name,
          depth, score, WDL). Helper: _formatPGNEvalAnnotation().
        - exportPGNToFile() + onPGNExported() for SAF-based PGN export.
        - _fileBrowserSelect() no longer calls showToast() after
          bridge.importSettings() — the onSettingsImported callback is
          the single source of truth for the import result toast,
          eliminating the duplicate-toast bug.
        - _safeExecute() wrapper in Java side catches
          RejectedExecutionException from engineExecutor and notifies
          JS via onEngineError (see StockfishNative.java).
        - restartCurrentEngine() and onEngineRestarting() both clear
          _reviewEvalCache, _multiPVLines, _multiPVResult,
          _lastEngineVariation to prevent stale evals from the old
          engine instance.
        - Ponder-Hit fix: uses JS-side cached _lastPonderMoveFromEngine
          instead of re-calling Java getLastPonderMove() (which is a
          one-shot read).
        - PV variation cache + fork grafting: _pvCache (Map) +
          _convertPVtoSANCached() + _checkPVDivergence(). Caches the
          converted SAN + post-state for every UCI prefix encountered
          during a single _processDeferredVariations() call, keyed by
          (state.hash, uciPrefix). MultiPV lines sharing a common prefix
          (e.g. e4 e5 Nf3) now convert the prefix exactly once instead
          of N times. Cache is cleared per-search (bounded at 200 entries).
        - generateFEN(): hoisted the PIECE_FEN lookup table to module
          scope (_PIECE_FEN) instead of allocating a fresh
          {white:{...},black:{...}} object on every call. generateFEN
          is called on every AI move, hint, and eval request.
        - _esc() / _escJs(): single-pass regex with callback + lookup
          map instead of 5 chained .replace() calls (5 intermediate
          string allocations → 1). These helpers are called on every
          move notation, file path, and ECO name during render.
        - _formatPGNEvalAnnotation(): explicit parenthesization of the
          mate-detection condition + Number() coercion of cached
          mate/eval values (defensive against JSON string values).
  - ui.js: GPL v3 (derived from DroidFish)
      UI layout and interaction patterns from DroidFish.
      Copyright (C) Peter Österlund. Modifications Copyright (C) 2026 Regalia.
      v1.0.2 additions:
        - startGame() now auto-fills ECO opening moves into moveRecords
          with proper SAN notation as it replays each move — the user
          sees the full opening sequence from move #1, no "..."
          placeholder needed.
        - _prependBlackToMovePlaceholder() called at 4 new-game entry
          points (startGame, _applyImportedFEN, exitSetup, importPGN).
        - redoMove() no longer calls doAIMove() — the redo stack
          contains pre-recorded moves; triggering a fresh AI search
          would corrupt the stack.
        - "Play Again" button now shows ⚔️ prefix.
        - executeMove() setTimeout(420ms) callback captures
          gameState.hash before the timeout and aborts if it changes,
          preventing stale callbacks from overwriting new state during
          undo/redo/flip (the "ghost game-over banner" bug).
        - doAIMove() moved out of the rAF callback into setTimeout(0)
          so the browser can paint the post-move UI before the engine
          starts thinking.
        - toggleSetup() simplified — removed dead 'play' status check.
        - infoCtrl now references the control-map entry directly
          instead of allocating a fresh {white,black} object per render.
        - _cachedBwrap liveness check changed from parentNode to
          document.body.contains() for stricter validation.
        - _updateSingleSq(): signature-based dirty check — builds a
          cheap signature string (piece + selection + last-move +
          check + legal + control-map + anim) and skips all DOM writes
          (style.background, className, innerHTML) when the signature
          hasn't changed. Previously rebuilt innerHTML for all 64
          squares on every engine-progress callback (~10-50/sec).
        - _getSqBg(): removed unused _sqBgCache declaration + dead
          lastFrom/lastTo computation (variables were computed but
          never used in the return value).
  - tablebase.js: GPL v3 (derived from DroidFish)
      PGN parsing logic (GameTree/PgnToken/PgnScanner) from DroidFish.
      Copyright (C) Peter Österlund. Modifications Copyright (C) 2026 Regalia.
      v1.0.2 additions:
        - _applyImportedFEN() and importPGN() call
          _prependBlackToMovePlaceholder() when the imported position
          has Black to move.
        - PGN variation continuation loop changed from `break` (truncate
          entire variation on first unparseable token) to `continue`
          (skip only that token, keep parsing the rest). moveAlg-based
          forgiving fallback applied uniformly to every token.
        - When an unparseable token is skipped, the side-to-move and
          move number now advance — a skipped move still consumes a
          turn per PGN spec, otherwise the next token would be
          attributed to the wrong side, desynchronizing the variation.
        - _tbCache (tablebase LRU cache) now refreshes on hit (delete +
          set) so frequently-accessed entries don't get evicted before
          cold entries. Previously only `get` was called without
          reordering, defeating LRU semantics.
  - ai-bridge.js: GPL v3 (derived from DroidFish)
      v1.0.2 additional fixes (second-pass review):
        - _formatVariationGroups(): variation line numbers are now assigned
          SEQUENTIALLY (1, 2, 3, ...) based on array position, not derived
          from group/mpvIndex/lineNum fields. The old scheme could collide
          (mainline=1, mpvIndex=0 also=1) producing duplicate "🌿线1"
          labels when both were attached to the same move (common after
          Flip or when multiple MultiPV lines diverge at the same move).
        - _checkPVDivergenceSANs(): added same-SAN dedup guard to prevent
          the same variation from being attached multiple times.
        - _mrToUci(): knight promotion letter 'k' → 'n' (UCI spec). Was
          causing false PV divergence for every knight promotion.
        - _resetGameUIState() in ui.js now resets isAIThinking,
          _aiSafetyTimerId, _aiRetryCount, _evalLoading, _sfEvalReady,
          _ponderGen, _ponderMoveSAN, _ponderBarInfo, _pendingPonderMoveUCI,
          _multiPVLines, _multiPVResult, _lastEngineVariation — prevents
          stale AI state from leaking into a new game (was causing "AI
          never moves" if the user started a new game during AI thinking).
        - onBestMove(): removed the `moveRecords.length > 0` guard so
          variations are tracked even when the AI plays the first move
          (player plays Black). Was causing no 🌿 variation lines for
          the AI's first move when playing Black.
        - _aiRetryCount reset added to onEngineReady() and
          onEngineRestarting() — prevents the retry counter from
          carrying over after a crash-recovery, which could immediately
          hit the 3-retry cap and show "AI timeout" despite the engine
          just having recovered.
        - onStatsRequestReview(): shows a toast when moveRecords is empty
          instead of silently returning.
        - _reviewEvalCache gains a peek() method (read without LRU
          refresh); iteration loops in _buildEvalTrendSVG,
          _findCriticalMoves, move-list render, and openStatsPage use
          peek() to avoid churning the Map.
        - openStatsPage() now also sends moveRecords (from/to/piece/
          captured/promotion/notation) in the payload — the stats page
          uses them to replay moves correctly instead of re-parsing the
          PGN string with its simplified parser (which cascade-failed
          on complex moves, capping the total move count).
        - Removed dead _checkPVDivergence(pv1, pv2) function (shadowed
          by the no-arg _checkPVDivergence() that iterates
          _pendingEnginePVs — JS last-declaration-wins rule made the
          former unreachable).
        - Removed onStatsRequestImport() and its export (stats import
          now stays inside StatsActivity).
        - executeMove() ponder-hit check: promotion piece name → UCI
          letter (queen→'q' etc.) so promotion moves can match the
          engine's UCI ponder move (was always failing, defeating
          ponder for all promotions).
        - makeMv() in game-logic.js: reuse capPiece for Zobrist hash
          instead of re-reading from original state (redundant read).
        - v1.0.2 (qw3.7max audit) — 7 optimizations from the external
          code-review report, all implemented:
          (1) _updateBoardLightweight(): state-comparison logic (_selChanged,
              _newHover→_infoChanged) rewritten with optional chaining (?.)
              for cleaner null-safe comparison; renamed _newHover to
              _infoChanged (the variable tracks info-square changes, not
              just hover).
          (2) Review move-classification span: _mcls.color and _mcls.label
              now wrapped in _esc() for defensive XSS protection (currently
              redundant since _classifyMove returns internal constants, but
              guards against future changes).
          (3) scrollIntoView behavior:'instant' → 'auto' at 2 call sites
              (review-mode auto-scroll) for broader compatibility with
              older WebView engines that don't support the CSSOM View
              'instant' value.
          (4) Review auto-scroll: rAF+setTimeout(0) → double rAF. The first
              rAF fires after layout, the second after paint — reading
              layout info (scrollIntoView) in the second rAF guarantees no
              forced synchronous layout (layout thrashing). The old
              rAF+setTimeout(0) pattern couldn't guarantee layout was
              complete because setTimeout is a macrotask that may run
              before the browser's layout/paint step.
          (5) _sqElCache: 2D array-of-arrays → 1D array indexed by (r*8+c).
              Single contiguous allocation, no nested array objects, one
              fewer pointer dereference per access. With 10-50 engine
              progress callbacks/sec, this shaves a small but measurable
              amount off the hot incremental-update path.
          (6) _isMoverWhite: ((i+1)%2)===1 → (i%2)===0 (mathematically
              equivalent, eliminates the unnecessary +1). Applied at 2
              sites in ui.js (review move-list render + _findCriticalMoves).
          (7) _rListEl: module-level cache of the review-moves-list element,
              avoids getElementById('reviewMovesList') on every render's
              scroll-into-view path. Assigned after full render, cleared on
              cache invalidation.
          (8) Review move-classification span: string concatenation (+=)
              → ES6 template literal for readability (the span is built
              once per reviewed move, not in a hot loop).
  - eco-data.js: AGPL v3 (original)
      ECO opening data from lichess-org/chess-openings (CC0).
      Code is original — not derived from DroidFish.
  - index.html.tpl: AGPL v3 (original CSS/HTML template)
  - build-chess.sh / build-chess.py: AGPL v3 (original build scripts)

v1.0.2 stats.html updates (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived PGN parsing):
  - parsePGN() now checks for _payload.moveRecords (sent by the main
    app). If present, calls parseFromMoveRecords() to replay the
    authoritative move list via executeMove() — avoids the simplified
    SAN parser's cascade-failure bug that capped total moves at ~98.
  - parseFromMoveRecords(): converts algebraic strings ("e2") to
    {row, col} objects (the main app stores from/to as strings; stats
    executeMove expects objects). Skips null placeholders.
  - renderPGNText() / renderSAN(): piece symbols now wrapped in their
    own <span class="piece-white/piece-black"> with the same
    color/stroke/glow as the main board. CSS specificity increased
    (.pgn-display .move .piece-white) so the piece color overrides
    .pgn-display .move. Previously the piece symbols were
    cream-colored (same as the rest of the move text) because
    .pgn-display .move (specificity 0,2,0) overrode .piece-white
    (specificity 0,1,0).
  - PGN import (📂 Select PGN File) now opens SAF picker directly
    from StatsActivity via statsSelectPGNFile() bridge method.
    onStatsPGNFileRead(content) callback updates the payload in place.
  - _statsPastePGN() no longer checks AndroidBridge.statsRequestImport
    (removed orphaned feature check).

The combined output (chess.html) is a combined work. The GPL v3 JavaScript
modules and AGPL v3 template retain their respective licenses. Since AGPL v3
imposes stricter requirements, its obligations effectively cover the entire
combined output.

See the root-level LICENSE-AGPL v3, LICENSE-GPL v3, and NOTICE files
for full license texts and attribution details.
